      <references>
	<title>Further topics</title>

  <p>
    Here are some topics and sources for independent study projects that are
    accessible at the level of this textbook.

    
<ul>    
  <li>The classification of the Platonic solids using group
    theory <xref ref="weylsymmetry"/></li>
  <li>More group theory with connections to geometry <xref ref="armstrong_groups_and_symmetry"/></li>
  <li>More group theory and an introduction to rings and fields <xref ref="gallian2017contemporary"/></li>
  <li>More geometry using a Kleinian approach <xref ref="henle_modern_geometries"/> </li>
  <li>An elementary introduction to the Hopf fibration <xref ref="elemhopf"/></li>  
  <li>Algebra and geometry in quantum mechanics <xref ref="nielsenchuang"/></li>

</ul>
    </p>

